Vice President Mike Pence administered the oath of office to the 18th United States Trade Representative, Robert Lighthizer. This completes President Donald Trump's Cabinet. Lighthizer is considered an expert on trade and has had a distinguished career in the field. He has represented American businesses as a trade litigator for the past 30 years. Lighthizer's appointment is seen as a move to fulfill Trump's promise of putting America first in trade. Lighthizer expressed gratitude for the opportunity to serve and praised the Trump administration's efforts in international trade.